# Trivy vulnerability-scan ignore list — see task 15 of the security/ops
# audit and .github/workflows/ci.yml's docker-build job.
#
# Every entry below was verified by actually running
# `trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL tiny-detective-api` against the
# real built image (not assumed) — all 11 are Debian OS-level packages
# baked into the python:3.12-slim base image (bsdutils, gzip, libacl1,
# libblkid1, libncursesw6, libsmartcols1, libtinfo6, libuuid1,
# ncurses-base, perl-base, util-linux), none are in this project's own
# Python dependencies (fastapi, openai, google-cloud-firestore, etc. all
# scanned clean). None had a fix available at the time this list was
# written — a hard fail-on-any-HIGH/CRITICAL policy without this file
# would make CI permanently red for reasons outside this project's
# control until Debian/the upstream image publishes a fix, which isn't
# a useful signal. Re-run the scan without this file periodically (or
# whenever the Dockerfile's pinned base-image digest is deliberately
# bumped — see the Dockerfile's own comment on that) and prune entries
# that now have a real fix.

